Description: Handle of Italian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.31, 44. The nearest parallel is ALBIAN on Athens, Agora SS9735; a similar example, retrograde, is noted from Brindisi by Desy, Ph., Les timbres amphoriques de l'Apulie republicaine (Oxford 1989) no. 787.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1265)
